### Describe the bug

I understand Blazor does not track void returning async methods. But I am noticing exceptions raised in methods returning Task are not caught by `ErrorBoundary`. 

In `MainLayout` I have added `ErrorBoundary` for the entire `@Body`. Now, in the VS project template, I am changing `Counter.razor`  to the following.

```CSharp

private void IncrementCount()
    {
        currentCount += IncrementAmount;

        ThrowException();
    }

    public async Task ThrowException()
    {
        await Task.Delay(100);
        throw new InvalidOperationException("Testing..");
    }

```

The above exception is not shown by `ErrorBoundary` or even in the browser yellow bar.

Making the following change (i.e. adding await) makes the browser's light yellow bar to appear.

```CSharp

private async void IncrementCount()
    {
        currentCount += IncrementAmount;

        await ThrowException();
    }

```

